Title: Learn C# with CSharpFritz - Ep9: SOLID Principles and Dependency Injection
Description:
We've covered the basics of the C# language, but have not yet gotten any practical advice on object design and interaction.  In this episode, Fritz talks about the SOLID design principles and applying them to C# classes and interfaces.  We conclude with a quick discussion of Dependency Injection and the ASP.NET Core dependency injection container.

Interactive Notebook with samples you can run IN BROWSER at:  https://aka.ms/csharpfritz_notebooks_2020

After the C# basics sessions are completed, which user interface framework do you want Fritz to walk through FIRST?  Vote for your favorite with an emote at:  https://github.com/csharpfritz/csharp_with_csharpfritz/issues/13

Questions:
0:23:25 - The nice thing about SOLID, the principles are applicable to any technology
0:53:14 - Composition is better than Inheritance
0:57:07 - At what point does DI become overengineered?
1:15:52 - How is the object lifetime affected if we use Dependency Injection?
1:35:51 - What about using "using statements" vs Dependency Injection?

Background Music is Harris Heller's Streambeats - Synthwave playlist, available royalty free at https://open.spotify.com/playlist/2gjWL0J5SQKceERGJ8Lb5e?si=hxqRoh0DSGei8eOu2vEsiA

Source code and interactive content from the stream are available at:  https://github.com/csharpfritz/csharp_with_csharpfritz
Watch live Mondays at 1300 UTC / 9a ET / 6a PT at:  https://twitch.tv/visualstudio
